   <talk_paragraph index="n087_beggar-accepting" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n087_beggar-accepting-a" mid="6"><![CDATA[<html> What's Telnumara like? </html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n087_beggar-accepting-b" mid="7"><![CDATA[<html> Tell me about the desert please </html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n087_beggar-accepting-c" mid="8"><![CDATA[<html> What's a mirage? </html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n087_beggar-accepting-d" mid="9"><![CDATA[<html> Why did a pirate go to the desert? </html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="5"><![CDATA[<html>$Ropi the Beggar$<BR>
You want to hear about the cities I’ve been to? Then I’ll tell you about the darn Telnumara. Telnumara is a city in a desert! Do you know how disgusting the desert is? It’s surrounded by sand. Nothing can live there. Only monsters and mirage can live there. </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n087_beggar-accepting-a" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_question mid="10"><![CDATA[<html>$Ropi the bum$<BR>I told you that Telnumara is a city in desert right? The heat is a living hell. The reason people can live there is because of the river nearby called Vasut River. If there wasn’t a river they will be all dead like the undead. </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n087_beggar-accepting-b" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_question mid="11"><![CDATA[<html>$Ropi the Beggar$<BR>
Desert is not the place where people can live. I still feel sick thinking of all that sand again. There is a ghost town near Telnumara. If ir wasn’t for that paper, I shouldn’t have gone to that ghost town. </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n087_beggar-accepting-c" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_question mid="12"><![CDATA[<html>$Ropi the Beggar$<BR>
Mirage is a illusion that lures people. If you get lured, you will end up dead walking around the desert. If there wasn’t writing on the paper saying follow the mirage to reach treasure, I wouldn’t have lost half of my men!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n087_beggar-accepting-d" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_question mid="13"><![CDATA[<html>$Ropi the Beggar$<BR>
Oh, smart question. That’s the point! That paper we found in Lotus Marsh said there were treasures in the Dark Overlord Tower. Going after that treasure was the stupidest thing I’ve ever done. </html>]]></talk_question>
